race.description: Remote Quality Care Service Country Mdn Hcp
race.comment: GOOD TIME (2) makes his debut for Brett Thompson and looks tuned up after a handy recent trial win at Wellington. Drawn to advantage for JPH and should measure right up. PENCILLER (6) showed speed from a wide draw at Narromine, leading for most of the trip before boxing on strongly for second over 1100m. Racing well and expected to be in this for a long way. ARGYLE SPRINGS (5) ran well on debut before a solid fourth at Wellington last start. Nearing peak now and is one to respect. SILVER CHAIR (7) returns and is a likely improver. Keeping safe from the good draw fresh. LOOKING THE PART (8) three-year-old gelding from the Cassandra Stummer stable on debut today. Watch for any market interest.
